<br>
Certainly what he says is vitriolic and some of it barely plausible nonsense- but in that respect he is little different from Rush Limbaugh, Sean Hannity or Fox News.  <br>
<br>
Fox News uses Oliver North (he of Iran-Contra infamy) as a military pundit, Moore used Marilyn Manson to comment on social issues in BF Columbine.  In both cases the sources seem singularly ill-equipped to discuss their message.  Of course some people won't find a problem with a lying traitor discussing &quot;honourable military conduct in war&quot;- just as others won't see an amoral musician discussing social trends as a big problem.<br>
<br>
One thing seems certain- the film will certainly provide food for thought for independent swing voters- the polarized extremes of political opinion have already pronounced judgement.  As demonstrated ably by Tsudanosh and Daetien on this thread(wtf is it about gnomes anyway)<br>
